oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Hartnack, Amanda

cesarean
dystocia
surgery
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A C-section is a surgery that can be performed in the field to resolve difficult dystocias. When used early in the calving process, it is possible to obtain positive results, including a live calf and a reproductively sound cow. Tips for maximizing success during these sometimes challenging procedures will be covered.
